03:43.787 --> 03:44.719
ever.

03:44.721 --> 03:46.054
Cold water.

04:28.660 --> 04:29.760
Lisa.

04:36.435 --> 04:39.841
Not a smart idea to go anywhere
today, pal, with all this fog.

04:40.543 --> 04:42.844
Stay inside, okay?

04:43.146 --> 04:44.846
Play some games with Robbie or

04:44.848 --> 04:46.181
practice your clarinet.

04:46.183 --> 04:47.738
I'm sure everyone else
in the neighborhood

04:47.764 --> 04:49.147
is staying inside today, too.

04:49.553 --> 04:50.852
Even the phones are out.

04:54.157 --> 04:55.556
Something wrong Lis?

04:55.558 --> 04:56.858
Hmm?

04:57.060 --> 04:58.459
No.

04:58.461 --> 04:59.060
No.

04:59.362 --> 05:00.595
Everything's fine.

05:01.297 --> 05:04.966
I mean, you wouldn't
believe me anyway so...

05:12.368 --> 05:16.168
<i>This is the story of Peter
and the wolf.</i>

05:16.580 --> 05:18.847
<i>Early one morning, Peter opened</i>

05:18.849 --> 05:22.917
<i>the gate and went out into
the big, green meadow.</i>

05:27.691 --> 05:29.557
Lisa!

05:29.560 --> 05:31.492
Come downstairs, will you?

05:31.594 --> 05:34.562
Your father and I
want to have a talk.

05:39.903 --> 05:40.669
Your mom says

05:40.671 --> 05:43.772
you've been acting kind of
funny all morning.

05:44.374 --> 05:46.475
Funny how?

05:47.277 --> 05:48.643
Well, for one thing,

05:48.645 --> 05:50.745
some clothes are missing
from the laundry.

05:50.747 --> 05:52.947
Do you know where they are?

05:54.351 --> 05:56.484
Honestly, I really don't know

05:56.486 --> 06:00.188
where they went.

06:00.190 --> 06:06.060
The truth is, they're
gone every day.

06:06.062 --> 06:09.964
And what does that mean,
"gone every day"?

06:10.266 --> 06:11.603
Okay,

06:12.229 --> 06:14.269
it's like mom's pancakes.

06:14.271 --> 06:15.637
Every morning, she makes them

06:15.639 --> 06:17.105
for breakfast, and you're always

06:17.107 --> 06:18.606
trying to fix the car, which for

06:18.608 --> 06:21.176
some mysterious reason has
always stopped running.

06:21.178 --> 06:23.077
Then, Mac and cheese for lunch.

06:23.079 --> 06:27.448
Then, we have meat loaf
for dinner every night.

06:27.450 --> 06:29.384
And at 8:00, we watch,

06:29.386 --> 06:31.085
"murder, she wrote" and go to

06:31.087 --> 06:36.558
bed, wake up tomorrow, and
do the exact same thing.

06:36.860 --> 06:39.690
Well, you and Robbie have school
tomorrow, and I have work, so...

06:39.696 --> 06:41.262
There is no school.

06:41.264 --> 06:42.530
There is no work.

06:42.532 --> 06:45.333
And what about your birthday?
That's not tomorrow either?

06:45.335 --> 06:46.400
No.

06:46.402 --> 06:47.902
Never comes.

06:47.904 --> 06:50.538
It's always the day
before I turn 16.

06:50.540 --> 06:52.407
It's pretty frustrating.

06:52.409 --> 06:54.709
I'm really trying to

06:54.711 --> 06:56.711
understand where this is
all coming from, pal.

06:57.713 --> 06:59.547
Are... are you bored
with your life?

06:59.749 --> 07:00.448
Is that it?

07:00.450 --> 07:02.417
I mean, are you anxious
about something?

07:02.619 --> 07:04.886
- Is it a boy?
- No, no, mum! God, no!

07:04.888 --> 07:07.121
You just don't understand it,
like, at all!

07:07.123 --> 07:08.289
Well, explain it to us.

07:08.291 --> 07:09.357
Maybe we can understand.

07:09.959 --> 07:11.860
That's the thing,

07:11.862 --> 07:13.728
is that I have tried to
explain it many times,

07:13.730 --> 07:16.431
and you guys just never remember
and you don't believe me.

07:16.433 --> 07:18.934
Believe what?

07:19.936 --> 07:21.302
That we're stuck in this house

07:21.504 --> 07:23.938
and we're never gonna leave.

07:23.940 --> 07:24.973
Why?

07:24.975 --> 07:25.940
Because all of us...

07:25.942 --> 07:27.642
Shut up, Lisa, shut up!

07:27.644 --> 07:29.644
Enough is enough, Lisa!

07:29.646 --> 07:31.512
Shh.

07:31.514 --> 07:32.347
Hey, hey.

07:32.349 --> 07:33.748
It's okay, buckaroo.

07:33.750 --> 07:34.182
Shh.

07:34.184 --> 07:36.351
Your sister is just
playing a silly game.

07:36.653 --> 07:40.688
Lisa, you tell your brother
that everything is okay.

07:40.990 --> 07:44.659
Lisa?

07:44.661 --> 07:47.729
I'm gonna go finish playing
the clarinet in my room.

07:48.131 --> 07:52.166
Let me know when the Mac
and cheese is ready.

08:30.006 --> 08:33.006
<i>Safe-deposit key...</i>

08:33.009 --> 08:36.210
<i>is that what you were looking
for, captain downing?</i>

08:36.212 --> 08:38.203
<i>Or should I say, Mr. downing</i>

08:38.230 --> 08:40.414
<i>or whatever your name is?</i>

08:46.265 --> 08:47.765
<i>Lisa Johnson.</i>

08:47.791 --> 08:50.091
<i>Me and Edgar found
the pirate treasure.</i>

08:50.093 --> 08:52.026
<i>Meet us down in the secret cave.</i>

08:52.028 --> 08:54.395
<i>We're gonna spend all
Sunday morning there.</i>

09:27.430 --> 09:28.623
Lisa?

09:28.699 --> 09:31.266
Go downstairs to the basement
and start the laundry, will you?

09:31.768 --> 09:33.101
I did it yesterday.

09:33.103 --> 09:34.869
